# Dart Code Standards

## General
- Use `final` and `const` everywhere possible
- Prefer named parameters for constructors with more than 2 parameters
- Use `sealed` classes for exhaustive pattern matching on domain states

## Models
- Use `freezed` for immutable data classes and unions
- Always implement `copyWith`, `==`, and `hashCode` via `freezed`

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
@freezed
class Room with _$Room {
  const factory Room({
    required String id,
    required String name,
    required int capacity,
  }) = _Room;

  factory Room.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$RoomFromJson(json);
}
```

## Async
- Use `Future`/`Stream` — never `async` without `await`
- Always handle errors: use `try/catch` or Riverpod's `AsyncValue.guard`

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
Future<void> bookRoom(String roomId) async {
  try {
    await _repository.book(roomId);
  } catch (e, st) {
    // log and rethrow or handle
    throw BookingException('Failed to book room $roomId', e);
  }
}
```

## Formatting
- Max line length: 80 characters (`dart format` enforced)
- No unused imports or variables
